<br>
Naturally, the SoD would be a bad idea for raiding or grouping *unless you are the tank* due to its impressive taunt effect.<br>
<br>
However, damage wise I have heard it procs extremely frequently making it a pretty amazing solo weapon.  <br>
<br>
My question is the following, assuming you got primal fistwraps, how good is this weapon for soloing ?<br>
<br>
Is it better than say Fists of Lightning ? Glowing Ulak ? and so forth ?<br>
<br>
Would love to see some data/opinions please.<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
M <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/20/02 7:06:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11506.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Anarchy in the SoD</span><hr size=1> Sod is silly rare on most servers, on Sol Ro if you can find one it will run you around 300k...  In general if you have a 15/20 or better weapon and nice haste item (41% or so) then I believe you will do better over all with the base damage.  Bottom line is that we hit so often that in general if you hit harder every hit you will be happier.  Procs in general do not average out as well, there are obvious postive and negative exceptions.  But my money is on better ratio and consistent damage.  <br>
<br>
