<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=71&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
That doesn't tell you anything about proc rate, sorry I can't help there.<br>
<br>
I will say though: Even if your suspicions are correct, and the proc rate would in fact yield more DPS when soloing/tanking than comparible NToV weapons, wouldn't you rather rather have a weapon you can use in all situations, solo, tanking, groups and raids?  If the proc makes it out-damage 15/20 weapons, it's unlikely to be so much as to be worth the 300k for such a small DPS upgrade.<br>
<br>
It's true value is in its taunt.  So if you duo with a cleric often in difficult encounters, and heal aggro prevents you from attempting encounters you think you could otherwise manage, then SoD would really shine.<br>
